The paper discusses the use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) for massive machine-type communications in 5G, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on IoT and machine-type communications also suggests the possibility of system-level design and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses simulation results and performance evaluation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG).
